comments.body:
Marking for 5.1.1 / 5.2.0, since it does not break anything and it is only a trace log. The compiler warning will be resolved using this solution: https://forums.developer.apple.com/thread/17921.

{quote}
After trying all the solution posted previously, I have found one that appears to work for the static library I work with.
 
- This is what I needed to change to Off to remove all the warnings
Precompile Prefix (Header GCC_PRECOMPILE_PREFIX_HEADER) = off
 
- Many people disussed that dysm had to be turned off, I believe it is working with it enabled
Debug Information Format (DEBUG_INFORMATION_FORMAT) = dwarf-with-dsym
 
- Since the enable bitcode is really to enable markers, we can just turn it off to remove warnings
Enable Bitcode (ENABLE_BITCODE) = NO
 
- This flag is needed to all builds will actually embed the bitcode
Other C Flags (OTHER_CFLAGS) = "-fembed-bitcode";
{quote}

[~fokkezb] please try [this version|https://github.com/appcelerator-modules/Ti.SafariDialog/releases/download/untagged-71327a0630e9922d798d/ti.safaridialog-iphone-1.0.3.zip] before I submit the PR. Thanks!
[~hansknoechel] I'd be happy to but that URL is 404 and the 1.0.3 release I can't find.
[~fokkezb], ok it was a draft release. [>>> Check it ouutttt heree!<<<|https://www.dropbox.com/s/owwj0gg1kuvdmdi/ti.safaridialog-iphone-1.0.3.zip?dl=0]
CR and FT approved. PR approved. Thanks Hans!

Verified fixed, using:

MacOS 10.11.2 (15C47a)
Studio 4.4.0.201511241829
Ti SDK 5.1.2.v20151124185220
Appc NPM 4.2.2
Appc CLI 5.1.0
Ti CLI 5.0.5
Alloy 1.7.26
Arrow 1.3.22
Xcode 7.1.1 (7B1005)
Node v0.12.7
Java 1.7.0_80
production

No warnings/errors appear when using the Ti.SafariDialog module. Tested using the 1.0.3 module and the example test provided with it.
